OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FITV News Political Editor Robert
OL,7,FPeston spent time with a focus group
OL,8,Fcommissioned by campaign group 38
OL,9,FDegrees, and carried out by JL
OL,10,FPartners, to hear how voters felt with
OL,11,Fthe eyes of the world focused on their
OL,12,FWigan constituency - spoiler, they
OL,13,Frather like it!
OL,15,FNo love lost for Starmer
OL,17,F"I can't stand him," said Pat, who is
OL,18,Fretired and breeds dogs, of the Prime
OL,19,FMinister Sir Keir Starmer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"He tells lies. He made promises to
OL,7,Fget to that position, and he's just
OL,8,Fbacktracked.
OL,10,F"He doesn't apologise, that's the
OL,11,Fother thing, and if something goes
OL,12,Fwrong, it's always somebody else's
OL,13,Ffault - it's never him."
OL,15,FPat voted Labour in the last election,
OL,16,Fand says she will vote Labour in next
OL,17,Fweek's byelection.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
