CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FHer dislike of the PM was a recurring
OL,7,Ftheme among the focus group, shared by
OL,8,Fboth Labour voters and those backing
OL,9,FReform and the Restore Britain Party
OL,10,Falike.
OL,12,FTracey, who works in social housing
OL,13,Fand is a Reform voter, shared this
OL,14,Fsentiment.
OL,16,F"I dislike him immensely," she said.
OL,18,F"I don't trust a word that comes out
OL,19,Fof his mouth. I don't think he's done
OL,20,Fanything good.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"Not that I particularly like the
OL,7,FTories... but I think it's got
OL,8,Fsignificantly worse since he's taken
OL,9,Fover."
OL,11,FAlex, a Reform voter and support
OL,12,Fworker, agreed.
OL,14,F"I just think he's hopeless. I don't
OL,15,Fthink he's done anything for us
OL,16,Faverage working people whatsoever.
OL,17,FNothing good to say about him."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
