OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FThe Labour Mayor of Greater
OL,7,FManchester, Andy Burnham, has made no
OL,8,Fsecret of the fact that if elected, he
OL,9,Fintends to challenge the prime
OL,10,Fminsiter for his premiership.
OL,12,FFormally announcing his intentions
OL,13,Fearlier this month, he told the people
OL,14,Fof Makerfield, "If I get your support,
OL,15,FI would seek to represent you at the
OL,16,Fhighest possible level and give this
OL,17,Fconstituency maximum power and
OL,18,Finfluence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"I think Wes Streeting seems to have
OL,7,Flaunched a leadership contest, so if
OL,8,Fthat is running, I would seek to join
OL,9,Fit."
OL,11,FThe voters ITV News spoke to seemed
OL,12,Flargely in agreement that Burnham
OL,13,Fwould be an improvement on the current
OL,14,FPM, but shared mixed feelings on his
OL,15,Frecord in Manchester.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FTracey admitted she found Burnham
OL,7,F"fairly likeable," but was critical of
OL,8,Fhis clean air initiatives. She also
OL,9,Fdescribed him as "very underhanded
OL,10,Fabout how he talks about things,"
OL,11,Fexplaining: "He'll not accept that
OL,12,Fhe's got something wrong."
OL,14,FSteve, a Conservative turned Reform
OL,15,Fvoter, owns a newsagent's shop in
OL,16,FMakerfield. He said Burnham
OL,17,Frepresented "more debt, more tax, and
OL,18,Fmore borrowing."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FHe went on to claim, "the national
OL,7,Fdebt will go up, so your tax will go
OL,8,Fup to pay for that."
OL,10,FSeveral individuals highlighted the
OL,11,FManchester mayor's personality as a
OL,12,Fmarked improvement on Starmer's, with
OL,13,FKieran saying: "I think we'd have more
OL,14,Fpersonality as a prime minister," if
OL,15,FBurnham secured the keys to Downing
OL,16,FStreet.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
