PN,30515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"He seems more human than the Starmer
OL,7,Fbot," said Kay, who works on the
OL,8,Frailways and helps distribute leaflets
OL,9,Fand flyers for Restore, having
OL,10,Fpreviously voted for Reform.
OL,12,FHannah, a senior quality control
OL,13,Fanalyst and Labour voter, thought the
OL,14,Fsame.
OL,16,F"I don't know if he's an upgrade," she
OL,17,Fsaid, "but it'd definitely be a change
OL,18,Ffrom Starmer, and he is going to be
OL,19,Fmore likeable."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FPat also thought Andy Burnham came
OL,7,Facross as more authentic, saying:
OL,8,F"Let's be honest, he's just... he's
OL,9,Fmore real."
OL,11,FReform's Robert Kenyon
OL,13,FAll reliable polling suggests the
OL,14,Ffight to be Makerfield's next MP will
OL,15,Fbe between Reform UK and Labour.
OL,17,FReform's candidate, plumber Rob
OL,18,FKenyon, is standing for a second time
OL,19,Fin the constituency, having previously
OL,20,Frun in 2024's general election and
OL,21,Fsince being elected as a councillor.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30517
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FWhile Kenyon frequently touts his
OL,7,Flocal credentials, our focus group
OL,8,Ffelt his inexperience stood out when
OL,9,Fcompared with Burnham.
OL,11,FPat liked that Kenyon could self-
OL,12,Fdescribe as a local resident, but
OL,13,Fvoiced concerns that, if elected, he
OL,14,Fwould "be eaten by the 'great big
OL,15,Fwhite sharks'.
OL,17,F"I think he could do really well...
OL,18,Fbut he's not got the experience."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30518
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FOlivia agreed, she would trust Andy
OL,7,FBurnham more in parliament "to be able
OL,8,Fto hold his own against other people,"
OL,9,Fthan any of the other candidates.
OL,11,FSteve, who intends to vote for Reform,
OL,12,Fadmitted he found the candidate Kenyon
OL,13,F"weak".
OL,15,FHe said: "They should have got a lot
OL,16,Fstronger candidate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30519
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"I mean, his past has been dragged up
OL,7,Fby several journalists, and I'm sure
OL,8,Fthat the Reform Party, knowing what a
OL,9,Fhigh-profile seat this is going to be,
OL,10,Fcould have picked a better candidate."
OL,12,FSteve referenced numerous social media
OL,13,Fposts found on old accounts of Rob
OL,14,FKenyon, which have been described as
OL,15,Fsexist, violent, and homophobic.
OL,16,FSeveral other unearthed posts have
OL,17,Fappeared to show him being vaccine
OL,18,Fsceptic and critical of Brexit - a
OL,19,Fcore issue for Reform voters.
OL,21,FVote splitter
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30520
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FIn a closely contested byelection,
OL,7,Fevery vote counts, with Kenyon's path
OL,8,Fto Westminster complicated by the
OL,9,Fsudden popularity of MP Rupert Lowe's
OL,10,FRestore Party in Makerfield.
OL,12,FSitting to the right of Reform on the
OL,13,Fpolitical spectrum, the party was
OL,14,Fformed after Lowe fell out with Nigel
OL,15,FFarage, leaving the Reform UK Party to
OL,16,Festablish his own.
OL,18,FIts candidate, Rebecca Shepherd, seems
OL,19,Flikely to draw votes away from Nigel
OL,20,FFarage's party, potentially easing
OL,21,FBurnham's path to power.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30521
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FTracey, who intends to vote for
OL,7,FReform, admitted that despite this,
OL,8,Fshe "actually really liked Rupert
OL,9,FLowe".
OL,11,F"I think he comes across very
OL,12,Fdifferently from a career politician,
OL,13,Fwhether you agree with his policies or
OL,14,Fnot," she said.
OL,16,F"The fact that he doesn't draw a
OL,17,Fsalary, I just really like him as a
OL,18,Fperson."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30522
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FHowever, highlighting the issue with
OL,7,FRestore standing in Makerfield, she
OL,8,Fcontinued: "I do think he's wrong to
OL,9,Fhave put his two pennies' worth into
OL,10,Fthis election.
OL,12,F"It should have been Reform against
OL,13,FLabour, and I think it's going to draw
OL,14,Fvotes away from Reform, which is
OL,15,Fprobably going to let Andy Burnham win.
OL,17,F"I think Rupert Lowe's a lot more
OL,18,Flikeable than Nigel Farage - I think
OL,19,Fit is going to definitely split the
OL,20,Fvote."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
