FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30523
SC,0023
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FKay says he has been surprised by the
OL,7,Fnumber of people who have told him on
OL,8,Fdoorsteps they will be voting for
OL,9,FReform on June 18.
OL,11,F"I've knocked on a lot of doors these
OL,12,Flast three weeks," he said.
OL,14,F"I was surprised by the amount of
OL,15,Fpeople who are going with Reform, not
OL,16,Fas a middle finger to Labour. It's as
OL,17,Fthough Reform are now actually a voice
OL,18,Ffor the working class, that Labour
OL,19,Fparted from us ten, 20 years ago."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G23/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30524
SC,0024
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FThe surprise felt by Kay arguably
OL,7,Fcomes from the sea of change in this
OL,8,FWigan constituency's allegiances.
OL,10,F"They always used to say, if you put a
OL,11,Fpig in a red Rosette, Wigan is going
OL,12,Fto vote for it - things have changed,"
OL,13,Fsaid Steve.
OL,15,FAll eyes on Makerfield
OL,17,FThe byelection in Makerfield is
OL,18,Funusual for the intense scrutiny and
OL,19,Fattention it is drawing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G24/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30525
SC,0025
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FWith Burnham's leadership ambitions
OL,7,Fclear, and a key part of his
OL,8,Fcampaigning, this comparatively small
OL,9,Fgroup of voters in the UK recognise
OL,10,Fthe responsibility casting their
OL,11,Fballot holds.
OL,13,F"It's a big responsibility," said Pat.
OL,15,F"I've spoken to my friends in America
OL,16,Fabout it. You know, they're saying,
OL,17,F'oh, you live there, don't you?' It's
OL,18,Fa huge responsibility because you
OL,19,Fcould change the fate of the country,
OL,20,Ftheoretically."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G25/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30526
SC,0026
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,FTracey described the reality of such
OL,7,Fintense campaigning: "Constant flyers,
OL,8,Fconstant phone calls, constant people
OL,9,Fknocking at the door.
OL,11,F"I actually said when I first found
OL,12,Fout about it, 'I sort of wish that it
OL,13,Fwasn't our constituency that was
OL,14,Fvoting,' because it's a lot of
OL,15,Fpressure.
OL,17,F"You're not voting for a byelection,
OL,18,Frealistically, you're voting for who's
OL,19,Fgoing to be the next PM."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G26/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30527
SC,0027
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781302284
OL,3,CWhat do voters in the UK's most
OL,4,Cconsequential byelection really think?
OL,6,F"It's the constant bombardment of it,"
OL,7,Fsaid Olivia, describing the sheer
OL,8,Famount of flyers and leaflets she
OL,9,Freceives.
OL,11,F"I had eight phone calls from
OL,12,Fdifferent survey companies trying to
OL,13,Fget research off me," she said,
OL,14,Fadding, however, that she hoped the
OL,15,Fintense scrutiny continued, whoever is
OL,16,Felected to represent them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G27/32
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
